Furthermore, such information, including the exhibit attached hereto, shall not be deemed incorporated by reference into any of the Company&#8217;s reports or filings with the SEC, whether made before or after the date hereof, except as expressly set forth by specific reference in such report or filing. The information in this Current Report on Form 8-K, including the exhibits attached hereto, shall not be deemed an admission as to the materiality of any information in this report on Form 8-K that is required to be disclosed solely to satisfy the requirements of Regulation FD.</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 182px; TOP: 110px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">This presentation as well as other written or oral communications made from time to time by us, may contain certain forward-looking information<br>
within the meaning of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, and the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended. These statements relate to future<br>
events or future predictions, including events or predictions relating to our future financial performance, and are generally identifiable by the use of<br>
forward-looking terminology such as &#8220;believes,&#8221; &#8220;expects,&#8221; &#8220;may,&#8221; &#8220;will,&#8221; &#8220;should,&#8221; &#8220;plan,&#8221; &#8220;intend,&#8221; &#8220;target,&#8221; or &#8220;anticipates&#8221; or the negative thereof<br>
or comparable terminology, or by discussion of strategy or goals that involve risks and uncertainties. These forward-looking statements are only<br>
predictions and estimates regarding future events and circumstances and involve known and unknown risks, uncertainties and other factors that may<br>
cause our actual results, levels of activity, performance or achievements to be materially different from any future results, levels of activity,<br>
performance or achievements expressed or implied by such forward-looking statements. This information is based on various assumptions by us that<br>
may not prove to be correct.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 7px">&#160;</font>Important factors to consider and evaluate in such forward-looking statements include:</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 312px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in the external competitive market factors that might impact our results of operations;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 332px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in laws and regulations, including without limitation changes in capital requirements under the federal prompt corrective action regulations;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 353px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in our business strategy or an inability to execute our strategy due to the occurrence of unanticipated events;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 393px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">the timing of acquisition or investment transactions;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 40px; TOP: 413px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">constraints on our ability to consummate an attractive acquisition or investment transaction because of significant competition for these<br>
opportunities;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 454px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">the failure of the Bank to complete any or all of the transactions described herein on the terms currently contemplated;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 474px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">local, regional and national economic conditions and events and the impact they may have on us and our customers;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 494px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">ability to attract deposits and other sources of liquidity;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 514px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in the financial performance and/or condition of our borrowers;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.3799; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 20px; TOP: 535px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in the level of non-performing and classified assets and charge-offs;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 35px; TOP: 555px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in estimates of future loan loss reserve requirements based upon the periodic review thereof under relevant regulatory and accounting<br>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 590px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">inflation, interest rate, securities market and monetary fluctuations;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 608px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">the timely development and acceptance of new banking products and services and perceived overall value of these products and services by users;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 904px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 625px; LEFT: 24px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">&#8226;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">changes in consumer spending, borrowing and saving habits;</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 379px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 415px; LEFT: 45px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Core Net Income ($mm)<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 9px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">(1)</font></font></div>

<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>loan (see GAAP to non-GAAP core reconciliation on page 35).</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 379px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 151px; LEFT: 502px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Net Interest Income ($mm)</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 877px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 103px; LEFT: 41px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ff0000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 22px">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Strategy execution has produced superior growth in revenues and<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font>core earnings</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 379px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 412px; LEFT: 502px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Income / Expense Growth<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 9px">&#160;</font>($mm)</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 311px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 146px; LEFT: 39px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Role of traditional bank branches<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>changing very rapidly</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 311px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 18px; TOP: 198px; LEFT: 39px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Mobile banking fastest growing channel</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 311px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 56px; TOP: 230px; LEFT: 39px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Banks of all sizes revisiting their<br>

<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>models and cost structures</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 311px; HEIGHT: 38px; TOP: 301px; LEFT: 39px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Technology &amp; customer needs, desires<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>and style changing rapidly</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 18px; TOP: 144px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Traditional CRE lending very difficult to do</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 177px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Very little consumer loan growth;<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>headwinds for consumer credit quality</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 18px; TOP: 228px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Growth exists only at niche players</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 261px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Mortgage banking revenues are<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>extremely volatile</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 313px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Pressure to reduce or eliminate Overdraft<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>and other nuisance fees by CFPB</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 323px; HEIGHT: 38px; TOP: 364px; LEFT: 603px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Regulators have no appreciation or<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>incentive to see banks grow profitability</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 328px; HEIGHT: 22px; TOP: 378px; LEFT: 27px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 14pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Business Issues</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 342px; HEIGHT: 22px; TOP: 420px; LEFT: 595px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 14pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Shareholder Expectations</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 326px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 56px; TOP: 452px; LEFT: 605px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Start bank and sell at 2 to 3x book no<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>longer an option - what do shareholders of<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>small privately held banks do?</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 326px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 523px; LEFT: 605px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Equity markets not available to small<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>banks</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 326px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 575px; LEFT: 605px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Banks need to earn 10% or more ROE if<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>they want to remain independent</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 326px; HEIGHT: 57px; TOP: 627px; LEFT: 605px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Consistent ROE of 12% or greater and<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>ROA of 1% or greater being rewarded well<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>by market</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 18px; TOP: 410px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Slow economic growth</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 443px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Low good quality consumer and business<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>loan demand</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 56px; TOP: 495px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Pressure continues on margin.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 9px">&#160;</font>Days of<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>3.5%-4.0% margin are gone.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 9px">&#160;</font>Banks need<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>to reduce efficiency ratios</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 18px; TOP: 566px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Difficult to attract good talent</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 37px; TOP: 598px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Very difficult and inconsistent<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 9px">&#160;</font>regulatory<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>environment</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 325px; HEIGHT: 57px; TOP: 650px; LEFT: 30px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Shareholders want 10%+ ROE, consistent<br>

<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 24px">&#160;</font>management infrastructure</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 161px; HEIGHT: 86px; TOP: 267px; LEFT: 399px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Issues facing<br>
Boards &amp;<br>
CEO&#8217;s</font></div>

for revenue and profitable<br>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 164px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Quality Asset Generation Remains A Challenge</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 218px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Low rate environment for the foreseeable future will continue to compress NIM</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 233px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Many institutions wither betting on rates or otherwise taking excessive interest rate risk</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 249px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Industry NIM continues to decline</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 264px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Down over 100 bps since 1995</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 280px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Low interest rate environment, competitive pressures likely to prevent return to historical levels</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 295px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Operational leverage</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 314px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Expense management is top of mind as banks try to improve efficiency in light of<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 6px">&#160;</font>revenue pressure and increased regulatory / compliance costs</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 329px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Regulatory pressure expected to stay robust</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 345px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">New Strategies</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 807px; HEIGHT: 15px; TOP: 364px; LEFT: 82px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Webdings; COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 5.6pt">4</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 11px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 8pt">Yesterdays strategies may not be appropriate tomorrow</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 699px; HEIGHT: 19px; TOP: 403px; LEFT: 127px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Critical to Have a Winning Business Model</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 193px; HEIGHT: 34px; TOP: 490px; LEFT: 149px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Heavy branch based delivery<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font>system</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 193px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 525px; LEFT: 149px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Strong credit quality</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 193px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 542px; LEFT: 149px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Core deposits</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 193px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 559px; LEFT: 149px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Dependent on OD fees</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 193px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 576px; LEFT: 149px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Expense management</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 188px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 449px; LEFT: 152px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Traditional Banks</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 198px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 492px; LEFT: 383px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Diversified revenue sources</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 198px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 509px; LEFT: 383px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Cross sell strength</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.44; WIDTH: 198px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 527px; LEFT: 383px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #c00000; FONT-SIZE: 7.2pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 14px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 9pt">Capital efficiency</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 192px; HEIGHT: 17px; TOP: 451px; LEFT: 385px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Fee Income Leaders</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: center; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 179px; HEIGHT: 35px; TOP: 441px; LEFT: 623px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #ffffff; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Relationship &amp; Innovative<br>
Banks</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 796px; HEIGHT: 32px; TOP: 22px; LEFT: 9px" nowrap>
<div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #01539a; FONT-SIZE: 20pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Our Approach to Developing a Winning Business </font></div>

<div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #01539a; FONT-SIZE: 20pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Model</font></div>
</div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 85px; TOP: 127px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">1.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 29px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Must focus on both &#8220;Relationship&#8221; or &#8220;High Touch&#8221; banking combined with<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 49px">&#160;</font>&#8220;Highly Efficient&#8221; or &#8220;High Tech&#8221;.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 13px">&#160;</font>Strategy should be unique as to not be copied<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 49px">&#160;</font>easily</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 85px; TOP: 227px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">2.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 29px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Attract and retain best high quality talent.<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 13px">&#160;</font>Business Bankers / Relationship<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 49px">&#160;</font>Bankers with approximately 15 years+ experience who bring a book of business<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 49px">&#160;</font>with them</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 327px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">3.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 29px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Compensate leaders based upon risk and profitability with both cash and equity</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 369px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">4.</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 29px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Never deviate from following critical success factors</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 411px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 40px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Only focus on very strong credit quality niches</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 453px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 40px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Have very strong risk management culture</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 56px; TOP: 495px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 40px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Have significantly lower efficiency ratio than peers to deliver sustainable<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 97px">&#160;</font>strong profitability and growth with lower margin and lower risk profile</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 13px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 566px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 40px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Always attract and retain top quality talent</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 897px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 608px; LEFT: 32px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">&#8226;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 40px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Culture of innovation and continuous improvement</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 761px; HEIGHT: 64px; TOP: 106px; LEFT: 99px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 20pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 20pt">Banks each year charge $32 billion in overdraft fees - that&#8217;s<br>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; MARGIN-TOP: 16px; WIDTH: 761px; HEIGHT: 32px; TOP: 298px; LEFT: 99px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 20pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 18px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 20pt">This is about 50% of all America spends on Food Stamps</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; WIDTH: 926px; HEIGHT: 57px; TOP: 132px; LEFT: 20px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 18pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">New no fee banking, 25 bps higher interest savings, line of credit, 55,000 ATM&#8217;s, Personal<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 30px">&#160;</font>Banker and more, all in the palm of your hand</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; MARGIN-TOP: 16px; WIDTH: 926px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 189px; LEFT: 20px" nowrap><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 18pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Marketing Strategy</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; MARGIN-TOP: 16px; WIDTH: 926px; HEIGHT: 57px; TOP: 234px; LEFT: 20px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 18pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Target technology dependent younger consumers; including underserved /<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 78px">&#160;</font>underbanked and middle income Americans</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; MARGIN-TOP: 16px; WIDTH: 926px; HEIGHT: 57px; TOP: 308px; LEFT: 20px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 18pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Capitalize on retaining at least 25% of our ~ one million student customers over a 5<br>
<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 78px">&#160;</font>year period</font></div>

<div style="POSITION: absolute; TEXT-ALIGN: left; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.2; MARGIN-TOP: 16px; WIDTH: 926px; HEIGHT: 28px; TOP: 381px; LEFT: 20px" nowrap><font style="DISPLAY: inline; HEIGHT: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 48px; FONT-SIZE: 0px">&#160;</font><font style="COLOR: #ee3e40; FONT-SIZE: 18pt" face="Wingdings">&#167;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 19px">&#160;</font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: Calibri; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 18pt">Reach middle income markets also through Affinity Banking Groups</font></div>

</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">CUSTOMERS BANCORP EXPECTS 2016 EARNINGS BETWEEN</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">$2.40 to $2.50 PER SHARE</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Wyomissing, PA &#8212; July 23, 2015 &#8212; Customers Bancorp, Inc. (NYSE: CUBI), the parent company of Customers Bank (collectively &#8220;Customers&#8221;), today provided guidance on management&#8217;s earnings estimates for the remainder of 2015 and for full year 2016. Customers expects earnings per share for the second half of 2015 to be $1.00 or more, resulting in earnings per share guidance for 2015 of $1.88, including a one-time special $6.0&#160;million provision for a potential fraud detected by the bank yesterday. Excluding this isolated event, 2015 earnings were expected to be over $2.00 &#160;per share.&#160;&#160;For 2016, Customers expects earnings per share of between $2.40 to $2.50 per share, a growth of about 20%.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#8220;We are very clear about our short term and long term goals and the strategies we will execute to achieve these goals. Our confidence in core operating earnings for 2015 and 2016 reflect our success in executing our &#8220;Single Point of Contact&#8221; business model, continuing to grow loans, deposits and fee based services and serve privately held businesses, high net worth families and strong mortgage companies across the United States, while we remain laser focused on Risk Management.&#160;&#160;We have attracted three new teams so far this year and expect them to be contributing to our profitability next year&#8221; stated Jay Sidhu, Chairman and CEO of Customers Bancorp, Inc.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Institutional Background</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Customers Bancorp, Inc. is a bank holding company located in Wyomissing, Pennsylvania engaged in banking and related businesses through its bank subsidiary, Customers Bank. Customers Bank is a community-based, full-service bank with assets of approximately $7.6 billion. A member of the Federal Reserve System and with deposits insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, Customers Bank provides a range of banking services to small and medium-sized businesses, professionals, individuals and families through offices in Pennsylvania, New York, Rhode Island, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, and New Jersey. Committed to fostering customer loyalty, Customers Bank uses a High Tech/High Touch strategy that includes use of industry-leading technology to provide customers better access to their money, as well as Concierge Banking&#174; by appointment at customers&#8217; homes or offices 12 hours a day, seven days a week. Customers Bank offers a continually expanding portfolio of loans to small businesses, multi-family projects, mortgage companies and consumers.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Customers Bancorp, Inc.'s voting common shares are listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol CUBI. Additional information about Customers Bancorp, Inc. can be found on the company's website,&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">www.customersbank.com</font>.</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block">&#160;</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-WEIGHT: bold">&#8220;Safe Harbor&#8221; Statement</font></div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block"><br>
</div>

<div style="TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">In addition to historical information, this press release may contain &#8220;forward-looking statements&#8221; within the meaning of the&#160;&#160;&#8220;safe harbor&#8221; provisions of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Numerous competitive, economic, regulatory, legal and technological factors, among others, could cause Customers Bancorp, Inc.&#8217;s financial performance to differ materially from the goals, plans, objectives, intentions and expectations expressed in such forward-looking statements. Customers Bancorp, Inc. cautions that the foregoing factors are not exclusive, and neither such factors nor any such forward-looking statement takes into account the impact of any future events. All forward-looking statements and information set forth herein are based on management's current beliefs and assumptions as of the date hereof and speak only as of the date they are made. For a more complete discussion of the assumptions, risks and uncertainties related to our business, you are encouraged to review Customers Bancorp, Inc.&#8217;s filings with the Securities and Exchange Commission, including its most recent annual report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31,&#160;&#160;2014 and subsequently filed quarterly reports on Form 10-Q.&#160;&#160;Customers Bancorp, Inc. does not undertake to update any forward-looking statement whether written or oral, that may be made from time to time by Customers Bancorp, Inc. or by or on behalf of Customers Bank.</font></div>
